08/06/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- A group of armed men late on Friday (June 6th) stormed the house of Prime Minister Hashim Thaci in Pristina, the police announced. Thaci was not home at the time, but his wife and his son were. Both escaped injury. The bodyguards injured at least one gunman. 
President Fatmir Sejdiu and the government sharply condemned the incident. The police announced on Sunday the arrest of a 19-year-old ethnic Albanian suspect. (BalkanWeb - 08/06/08; AP, ITAR-TASS, Reuters, AFP, BBC, RIA Novosti - 07/06/08)
